Despite acquiring over 240 acres of property since FY 2016, the Department of Parks and Recreation has consistently received under 0.60 percent of New York City’s operating budget

The FY 2025 preliminary budget for the Department of Parks and Recration is $583.7M, representing 0.53 percent of New York City’s preliminary operating budget.
